The paper also discusses the use of a siamese architecture and triplet loss, which are common techniques in deep learning for similarity-based tasks, suggesting that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also addresses issues with training data and architecture, indicating a focus on machine learning and optimization, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of product quantization for compression, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
